                            <comment id="28631" author="pjones" created="Tue, 14 Feb 2012 11:29:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brent&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we do end up adding RHEL6.2 support for 1.8.x it will be tracked under a ticket for a more current RHEL6.2 kernel update&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="28494" author="fprimex" created="Mon, 13 Feb 2012 10:59:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could this issue be reopened? While RHEL 6.2 support for Lustre 2.x appears to be progressing, there still has not been an updated release for 1.8.x.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="24887" author="ys" created="Fri, 16 Dec 2011 13:04:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;RHEL6.2 work will trace in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-781&quot; title=&quot;Kernel update [RHEL6.2 2.6.32-220.el6]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-781&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-781&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="24090" author="ys" created="Mon, 12 Dec 2011 10:51:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Many thanks for the URL. I have working on FC15 support, it also help RhEL6.2 work. And i&apos;ll switch to work on rhel6.2 support shortly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="24088" author="waschk" created="Mon, 12 Dec 2011 09:48:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any ETA on a patch for this? There is already a RHEL6.2 kernel release which will be the base for the next security update. It wouldn&apos;t be nice if we had to disable lustre after the next update. You can get a binary package of the latest kernel vom Scientific Linux:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://ftp.scientificlinux.org/linux/scientific/6rolling/x86_64/updates/security/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://ftp.scientificlinux.org/linux/scientific/6rolling/x86_64/updates/security/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="22049" author="pjones" created="Thu, 27 Oct 2011 12:06:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yangsheng will be working on RHEL6.2 support&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
